   <documentation>
      <row>
         <Docu><![CDATA[=Execute SQLPlus=

Executes a command script or file using SQLPlus. The command is piped into the SQLPlus tool by "echo" command. By that you have the possibility to cover e.g. the following scenarios:
 - execute an arbitrary sql-script file using the command "@/home/myuser/myscript.sql". The call of SQLPlus would look like e.g.: "echo @/home/myuser/myscript.sql | sqlplus username/password@ORCL"
 - to execute a select-statetement set the parameter e.g. to "select * from dual;"
 - start the DB by setting the parameter to "startup;"
 - stop the DB by setting the parameter to "shutdown immediate;"

=Output=
In any kind of error (e.g. ORACLE returned an error or the action can not execute the sqlplus command,..) the action should fail. There are 2 output parameters as following: 
  1. UC4RB_OUT_ORCL_STATUS_CODE#	Contains the Oracle status code, in case of errors during the execution. E.g. ORA-01081
  2. UC4RB_OUT_ORCL_MESSAGE_DESCR# Contains the Oracle status message, if there was an error returned by Oracle. E.g. "Cannot start already-running ORACLE - shut it down first"]]></Docu>
      </row>
